BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Putting Social Determinants into Practice: How CHRs Strengthen Tri
 bal Diabetes Programs
DTSTART;TZID=Eastern Time:20260708T130000
DTEND;TZID=Eastern Time:20260708T160000
DTSTAMP:20260704T224116
UID:1783226476186.CFLIB.ORG
CLASS:PUBLIC
DESCRIPTION:This session explores how Community Health Representatives can
  use their unique position as trusted community members to identify and ad
 dress the social determinants of health that drive diabetes outcomes in tr
 ibal communities. Participants will gain a working understanding of the fi
 ve SDOH domains -- economic stability\, education\, healthcare access\, ne
 ighborhood environment\, and social context -- and how each directly affec
 ts diabetes self-management and clinical outcomes. Through three real-worl
 d case studies and discussion\, the session demonstrates practical CHR str
 ategies for screening\, connecting patients to resources\, and communicati
 ng social needs to the care team. Attendees will leave with actionable too
 ls\, including guidance on the PRAPARE screening instrument and referral p
 athway development\, along with a personal SDOH action plan to implement i
 n their programs. JOIN WEBEX WEBINAR https://hhs-ihs.webex.com/hhs-ihs/j.p
 hp?MTID=m58d25987b9aa6e351ddfc872fc5599b2 Webinar number (access code): 28
 37 318 0868 Webinar password: 6XRyYtFmS33(69799836 from phones and video s
 ystems) TAP TO JOIN FROM A MOBILE DEVICE (ATTENDEES ONLY) +1-1-415-527-503
 5\,\,28373180868 & tel:%2B1-1-415-527-5035\,\,*01*28373180868%2369799836%2
 3*01* United States Toll Some mobile devices may ask attendees to enter a 
 numeric password. JOIN BY PHONE +1-1-415-527-5035 United States Toll Globa
 l call-in numbers https://hhs-ihs.webex.com/hhs-ihs/globalcallin.php?MTID=
 m2b64717992910ebb1f44fa614c86ee29 Can&chr(39)t join the webinar? https://c
 ollaborationhelp.cisco.com/article/WBX000029055 IMPORTANT NOTICE: Please n
 ote that this Webex service allows audio and other information sent during
  the session to be recorded\, which may be discoverable in a legal matter.
  By joining this session\, you automatically consent to such recordings. I
 f you do not consent to being recorded\, discuss your concerns with the ho
