BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Small Shifts\, Big Impact: Integrating Nutrition Standards\, CKM C
 are\, and Nutrition-Focused Medication Management in Diabetes
DTSTART;TZID=Eastern Time:20260923T130000
DTEND;TZID=Eastern Time:20260923T160000
DTSTAMP:20260704T224120
UID:1783226480707.CFLIB.ORG
CLASS:PUBLIC
DESCRIPTION:This presentation will review current standards of care in dia
 betes nutrition and highlight CKM-focused dietary strategies to address in
 terconnected cardiometabolic and kidney health risks. Participants will ex
 plore key nutrition considerations across common glucose-lowering medicati
 ons\, including SGLT2 inhibitors\, metformin\, GLP-1 receptor agonists and
  insulin to align care plans with patient needs. Emphasis is placed on cul
 turally responsive\, patient-centered approaches\, including the "small sh
 ifts" framework to support sustainable nutrition and lifestyle changes. At
 tendees will leave with actionable strategies to enhance diabetes care for
  the communities they serve. JOIN WEBEX WEBINAR https://hhs-ihs.webex.com/
 hhs-ihs/j.php?MTID=m6352d34aa233c6c3b477ff6155f81c97 Webinar number (acces
 s code): 2819 364 5518 Webinar password: mMRq7FS5J3n(66777375 from phones 
 and video systems) TAP TO JOIN FROM A MOBILE DEVICE (ATTENDEES ONLY) +1-1-
 415-527-5035\,\,28193645518 & tel:%2B1-1-415-527-5035\,\,*01*28193645518%2
