BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Trauma\, Nutrition\, and Metabolic Resilience: Implications for Di
 abetes Prevention and Care
DTSTART;TZID=Eastern Time:20261007T130000
DTEND;TZID=Eastern Time:20261007T160000
DTSTAMP:20260704T224123
UID:1783226483788.CFLIB.ORG
CLASS:PUBLIC
DESCRIPTION:This session presents an integrated\, trauma-informed approach
  to diabetes care and prevention\, highlighting the connections between st
 ress physiology\, metabolic resilience\, and diabetes outcomes. When stres
 s physiology becomes persistent\, it can contribute to insulin resistance\
 , glycemic instability\, and increased risk for the development or progres
 sion of type 2 diabetes. Participants will gain practical insight into how
  targeted nutrition strategies can support both healing and improved glyce
 mic management. JOIN WEBEX WEBINAR https://hhs-ihs.webex.com/hhs-ihs/j.php
 ?MTID=m5733b064cb98d76b1092d4676c8483f7 Webinar number (access code): 2833
  957 4430 Webinar password: UdSPJXjA267(83775952 from phones and video sys
 tems) TAP TO JOIN FROM A MOBILE DEVICE (ATTENDEES ONLY) +1-1-415-527-5035\
 ,\,28339574430 & tel:%2B1-1-415-527-5035\,\,*01*28339574430%2383775952%23*
 01* United States Toll Some mobile devices may ask attendees to enter a nu
 meric password. JOIN BY PHONE +1-1-415-527-5035 United States Toll Global 
